    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera 4S (996.2) is a superlative example of the widebody naturally aspirated flat-six era. Powered by the 3.6L M96.03 boxer engine featuring VarioCam Plus, the power delivery is linear and robust. The Getrag G96/31 six-speed manual gearbox offers crisp, short-throw engagement, driving the all-wheel-drive system with a rear-biased torque split. Mechanically, this unit is impeccable: the IMS bearing and Rear Main Seal (RMS) have been proactively addressed with documented LN Engineering components. The suspension geometry remains factory-spec, featuring the C4S-specific stiffened chassis and Turbo-derived braking system with four-piston monobloc calipers and cross-drilled rotors. Cosmetically, the Basalt Black Metallic finish retains its deep luster with zero evidence of clear-coat failure, while the interior leather shows no bolster wear or UV degradation. This is a collector-grade chassis for the discerning purist.",
      "price": 44900.0,
      "reputation": 0.4,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 45
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_3_listing_3",
      "firm_id": "sybil_3",
      "description": "Mint condition. Garage kept. No accidents. Clean title. Full service history. Inspection welcome.",
      "price": 42500.0,
      "reputation": 0.3,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
